{
  "texts": [
    "A higher SSIM score signifies a greater resemblance between the images, reflecting a minimal loss in perceived image quality.",
    "The Spectral Angle Mapper (SAM) technique evaluates spectral similarity by measuring the angle between spectra from a sample and an image as vectors.",
    "This angle quantifies how closely the two spectra match, indicating similarity in material composition.",
    "A smaller angle suggests a high degree of similarity, implying a good match between the sample and image properties (Han et al. 2018a).",
    "Hyperspectral image reconstruction, an emerging field of scientific research, has seen significant advancements through efforts like the NTIRE spectral reconstruction challenges (Arad et al. 2020 (Arad et al., 2022))."
  ]
}